40 Li occhi da Dio diletti e venerati, 41 fissi ne l’orator, ne dimostraro 42 quanto i devoti prieghi le son grati;
43 indi a l’etterno lume s’addrizzaro, 44 nel qual non si dee creder che s’invii 45 per creatura l’occhio tanto chiaro.

query.result:
**English:**
40 Her eyes, beloved and revered by God, 41 fixed on the speaker, showed 42 how pleasing to her are devout prayers;
43 then they turned to the eternal light, 44 into which it is not to be believed that 45 the eye, however clear, can penetrate by its own power.
**Sanskrit:**
40 Tasyā devapriyāḥ pūjitāśca netrī, 41 vaktr̥iṇi niviṣṭe darśitavān, 42 yāvat bhaktaprārthanāḥ asyai priyāḥ santi;
43 tataḥ śāśvataprakāśam abhito nirikṣitavān, 44 yasmin na śraddadhītaṃ yathā 45 svata eva prakāśamānasya netrasyāpi praviśati.

